Build Your Einstein Classification Model

After you configure the predictive model, its status changes to Ready to Build. Check your Fields to Predict and build your model.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.
View Setup
Customize Application
Manage Profiles and Permission Sets
Edit on cases OR Modify All Data

As Einstein completes learning for each field, the model’s owner is notified about build progress. To check if the build is completed, visit the Einstein Classification Setup page.

To build a model, on the Setup page, select the model name.
Click the model’s Setup tab.
The Fields to Predict section lists the fields whose values Einstein predicts. To remove a field from the model, click Remove in the field’s action menu. To add fields, click Edit under Configure Data.
Build the model.
Einstein starts analyzing your closed cases and building the model for the fields you selected.

After the model finishes building, you can configure each field’s prediction settings. Then, activate the model to start showing recommendations in the Service Console. After the initial build date, Einstein retrains your model every 30 days.

NOTE You can’t pause a model build, but you can update the model’s settings after it’s built.
title: Building and Automating Classification Models in Service Cloud
